title.rendered: New Zealand vs Sri Lanka, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Cricket Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Reports & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable New Zealand & Sri Lanka Playing XIs

New Zealand: Bernadine Bezuidenhout (wk), Suzie Bates, Georgia Plimmer, Amelia Kerr, Sophie Devine (c), Maddy Green, Hannah Rowe, Lea Tahuhu, Jess Kerr, Eden Carson, Molly Penfold

Sri Lanka: Harshitha Samarawickrama, Chamari Athapaththu (c), Vishmi Gunaratne, Anushka Sanjeewani (wk), Nilakshi de Silva, Malsha Shehani, Oshadi Ranasinghe, Ama Kanchana, Sugandika Kumari, Inoka Ranaweera, Achini Kulasuriya

Pitch Report for Boland Park, Paarl

Venue: Boland Park, Paarl

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 137

2nd innings average score: 98

Wickets per innings: 89

Type: Good for bowling

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Also Read:

India vs Ireland, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023 Fantasy Cricket Tips

Quetta vs Peshawar, Pakistan T20 League 2023 Fantasy Cricket Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Suzie Bates and Sophie Devine love facing Sri Lanka. While Bates has 300 runs at 37.5 and 5 wickets, Devine has 203 runs at 29 and 6 wickets.

Inoka Ranaweera has seven wickets in the last five T20Is against New Zealand. Overall, she has gone wicketless in only one of the last 10 T20Is, scalping 17 wickets.

Chamari Athapaththu has scored 196 runs at 21.8 but has picked only three wickets against New Zealand.

Maddy Green has generated the 30-run bonus in five of the last nine matches. She averaged 59.8 during this period.

Eden Carson is having a dream start to her T20I career. She has taken at least one wicket in seven of her 11 games so far, along with generating bonus points for economy.

Lea Tahuhu has picked 14 wickets in her last six T20Is.

Harshitha Samarawickrama averages 61 in the last 5 T20s.

In each of the last three games at the venue, at least one team has been bowled out.
